                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-279-off1558 t18270913-279-crimeloc1560"></join>. On the 11th of September, the prisoner was there, at work with others, white-washing the house - I lost a spoon off the shelf in the kitchen.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-279-person2208">
                  GEORGE 
                  ELIAS LAZARUS
               <interp inst="t18270913-279-person2208" type="surname" value="ELIAS LAZARUS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-279-person2208" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-279-person2208" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a silversmith, and live at No. 10, Broad-street, Bloomsbury. On Tuesday, the 11th of September, the prisoner brought this spoon to sell, between two and three o'clock - I asked where he got it; he said he found it among some rubbish - I said that could not be, he had better go and get the owner; he went and brought Winsland, who said it was Mr. Wharton's.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-279-person2209">
                  NICHOLAS 
                  WINSLAND
               <interp inst="t18270913-279-person2209" type="surname" value="WINSLAND"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-279-person2209" type="given" value="NICHOLAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-279-person2209" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a painter. I met the prisoner, who had worked for me; he came into my house, and confessed that he had stolen the spoon - I went with him to Lazarus, and told what he had said.</p>
               <p>The prisoner received a good character.</p>
